  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A comparison of chest x-ray (CXR) and Minimum dose CT (MnDCT) in the acutely ill patient. The
      hypothesis is that MnDCT is more sensitive than CXR in the detection of acute findings in the
      acutely ill patient.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A comparison of chest x-ray (CXR) and Minimum dose CT (MnDCT) in a cohort of 100 patients
      admitted for acute respiratory distress. Chest radiography (CXR) is compared to Minimum Dose
      CT (MnDCT) for the detection of consolidation;lung nodules, heart failure.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
